The SVM model achieved high accuracy in classifying breast cancer cases, showing its effectiveness for medical datasets. Feature scaling played a crucial role in improving the model's performance, as SVM is sensitive to feature magnitudes. The RBF kernel allowed the model to capture non-linear relationships within the data, leading to better predictions. The confusion matrix showed very few misclassifications, indicating strong generalization. Overall, SVM proved to be a reliable and robust algorithm for this classification problem.
